HEADWORD: Syntonize
<hw>Syn"to*nize</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>-nized</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>-nizing</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[See
<er>Syntony</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Physics)</fld> <def>To adjust or devise
so as to emit or respond to electric oscillations of a certain wave
length; to tune; specif., to put (two or more instruments or systems of
wireless telegraphy) in syntony with each other.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Syn`to*ni*za"tion</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
